---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="The Weekend Watch: Hamilton Jazzmaster Chrono Quartz" description="Hamilton Jazzmaster Chrono H32612731 — sporty refinement for the man who works hard and plays harder.">
  <article class="story-article">
    <header class="story-header">
      <div class="story-category">Everyday Luxury</div>
      <h1>The Weekend Watch</h1>
      <div class="story-meta-line">
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>Hamilton</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="story-hero-img">
      <img src="https://cdnstatic.creationwatches.com/products/product-images/l/H32612731_LRG.webp" alt="Hamilton Jazzmaster Chrono H32612731" />
    </div>

    <div class="story-body">
      <p class="story-lede">
        There are watches for boardrooms, and there are watches for the beach. Then there's the Jazzmaster Chrono — the rare watch that refuses to choose. Built for the man whose weekend is just as important as his work week.
      </p>

      <h2>The Best of Both Worlds</h2>
      <p>
        The Jazzmaster Chrono H32612731 bridges two worlds effortlessly. Its traditional round case and clean dial design satisfy the classicist in you. The chronograph pushers and sporty orange accents speak to your adventurous side. It's a Jekyll-and-Hyde watch that transforms based on what you pair it with — a suit, a polo, or a wetsuit.
      </p>
      <p>
        At 44mm, this watch has presence. The unidirectional bezel adds a dive-watch edge while the chronograph function brings motorsport timing precision. It's a fusion of styles that somehow works perfectly — proof that Hamilton's designers understand how modern men actually live.
      </p>

      <h2>Quartz Precision, Hamilton Soul</h2>
      <p>
        While purists debate mechanical versus quartz, the H32612731 makes a compelling case for quartz. It's accurate to within seconds per month, requires no winding or resetting after weekends off, and costs a fraction of its automatic siblings to service. For someone who wants Hamilton quality without the mechanical maintenance, this is the sweet spot.
      </p>
      <p>
        The chronograph function is crisp and responsive — start, stop, reset with a satisfying click. Use it to time your morning run, your parking meter, or simply as a conversation starter. The 100-meter water resistance means you won't have to think twice about wearing it into the pool.
      </p>

      <h2>Built for Real Life</h2>
      <p>
        What makes this watch special is how it wears over time. The stainless steel case develops a subtle patina of micro-scratches that give it character. The bracelet drapes comfortably on the wrist, conforming to your shape after a few days. It's a watch that becomes part of you — not because of any single feature, but because of how it integrates into your daily life.
      </p>

      <blockquote class="story-quote">
        "The Jazzmaster Chrono is the watch you reach for when you don't want to think about what watch to wear. It works with everything, goes everywhere, and never lets you down."
      </blockquote>

      <div class="story-specs">
        <h3>At a Glance: Hamilton Jazzmaster Chrono H32612731</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Movement:</strong> Swiss Quartz (chronograph)</li>
          <li><strong>Case:</strong> Stainless steel, 44mm</li>
          <li><strong>Crystal:</strong> Sapphire with anti-reflective coating</li>
          <li><strong>Bezel:</strong> Unidirectional, black with orange accents</li>
          <li><strong>Dial:</strong> Black with luminous hands and markers</li>
          <li><strong>Functions:</strong> Chronograph, date, 24-hour indicator</li>
          <li><strong>Water Resistance:</strong> 100m (330ft)</li>
          <li><strong>Strap:</strong> Stainless steel bracelet with safety clasp</li>
          <li><strong>Price:</strong> $543.79</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="story-cta">
        <p>This piece and hundreds more are waiting to become part of your story.</p>
        <a href="/stories" class="btn">Explore More Stories</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .story-article { max-width: 750px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 1.5rem; }
  .story-header { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .story-category { font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-accent); margin-bottom: 1rem; font-weight: 500; }
  .story-header h1 { font-size: 2.5rem; line-height: 1.2; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .story-meta-line { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-muted); display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .story-hero-img { margin: 0 -1.5rem 3rem; text-align: center; background: var(--color-border); padding: 2rem; }
  .story-hero-img img { max-width: 300px; height: auto; }
  .story-body { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.9; color: var(--color-text); }
  .story-lede { font-size: 1.15rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-muted); font-style: italic; margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-left: 1rem; border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent); }
  .story-body h2 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.5rem; margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .story-body p { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .story-quote { margin: 2.5rem 0; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; background: #f5f0e8; border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent); font-style: italic; font-size: 1.05rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--color-text); border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0; }
  .story-specs { margin: 2.5rem 0; padding: 2rem; background: #faf8f5; border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-radius: 8px; }
  .story-specs h3 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .story-specs ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
  .story-specs li { padding: 0.4rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  .story-specs li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .story-cta { text-align: center; margin-top: 3rem; padding: 2rem; background: linear-gradient(to bottom, transparent, var(--color-border)); border-radius: 8px; }
  .story-cta p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .story-article { padding: 2rem 1rem; }
    .story-header h1 { font-size: 1.8rem; }
  }
</style>
